<br>
That being said, my suggestion wasn't about cities having Arenas.  That actually serves no purpose except for those of the same 'alignment' (so to speak) that want to RP a duel.  Granted, dark elves can make it through Freeport to the arena, but that's about it.  I don't believe that Trolls can, at least not without a bit of faction work.  I know plenty that were KoS by default.  What evil races can get in Halas (or would want to), Rivervale or Qeynos?  What good races can get into Neriak or Cabilis?  I don't mean invising in and all that jazz, I mean simply arranging for a PvP type encounter?  That pretty much leaves The Arena for having any 'fair' combat RPed out.  Not exactly convenient for spur of the minute action.<br>
<br>
I agree that making at least an Arena available in the newbie zones near cities (and one in GF) would at least provide for the opportunity for larger battles to take place.<br>
<br>
Do you have to have PvP to roleplay?  No.  But there are a lot of things you don't have to have.  I'm not talking realism as in the real world, I am talking about realism as in the opportunity to provide a forum that makes more sense for those that want larger scale battles (or those smaller scale chance encounters) but don't want to go to The Arena to do it.  It wouldn't impede on anyone else's fun, but would provide for something that would equate to the encounters one might find in a fantasy novel or movie.  That's all.<br>
<br>
There are plenty of things that aren't realistic about EQ, and there are plenty of things that are put in for the sake of realism that don't enhance the game.  <br>
<br>
I was in many roleplaying stories when Bristlebane first opened.  That was back when all duels were broadcast serverwide, for those that are newer to the game.  It was quite annoying to have ambushes and large scale encounters that involved creative dueling.  Yes, we did the best we could, but it would have been so much nicer to have the opportunity to have group combat instead of lots of single duels.  Am I saying the game <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> has</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to have something better?  No.  But I think the game could have something better that wouldn't impede on anyone else. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uskybyrd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Skybyrd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/22/01 4:36:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Roleplaying without PvP?</span><hr size=1> I saw a bit of wrong thinking here:<br>
<br>
Gnome goes running, Vachir asks why does the gnome run when he knows the Ogre can't do anything..<br>
<br>
Cause, Vachir, the Gnome *DOESN'T* know... the guy behind the keyboard knows.  Same with the other scenario... It's called *roleplaying*.  We are playing as *our characters* acting as if we were in Norrath, if Norrath were real.  That means sometimes we ignore game knowledge in favor of acting like our characters would.  Playing a gnome, running across an OGRE, damn right I would run like hell!  Seeing a dark elf would make me do the same thing.  <br>
